 If it's large, that's fine, but including that resource could create a need. It might be better to use a non-existent resource path with a unique name for the system branch. I could assert it doesn't exist and handle a FileNotFoundException. This approach seems to satisfy any concerns about \\\"remaining uncovered call sites.\\\"\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Ligmk7cvNjOkhnhII0UoMwRS|fc_017742b190de04280169f58e143d5881a0a0f5b943a8c0ace2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_core/ClassPathResourceTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\n", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\nimport java.io.FileNotFoundException;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\n"}, {"oldText": "    void resolvesResourceThroughSystemClassLoaderFallback() throws IOException {\n        ClassPathResource resource = new SystemLookupClassPathResource(ABSOLUTE_RESOURCE_PATH);\n\n        assertReadableResource(resource);\n    }\n", "newText": "    void reportsMissingResourceThroughSystemClassLoaderFallback() {\n        ClassPathResource resource = new SystemLookupClassPathResource(\n                \"org_springframework/spring_core/missing-class-path-resource-test.txt\"\n        );\n\n        assertThat(resource.exists()).isFalse();\n        assertThatThrownBy(resource::getInputStream)\n                .isInstanceOf(FileNotFoundException.class)\n                .hasMessageContaining(\"does not exist\");\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 447, "output": 1582, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16877, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopR