[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying ClassLoader use**\n\nI'm thinking about how the Gradle test worker uses the application ClassLoader. I believe the system class loader is usually a URLClassLoader. But it seems for Gradle, the test classes might be in the application classloader? I'm wondering if the JUnit test ClassLoader could be the same as the system class loader. Oh, I just realized the Gradle worker actually uses a VisitableURLClassLoader, not the system one as I'd originally thought!\n\n**Considering system resources**\n\nI'm thinking about system resources, specifically if \"java/lang/String.class\" is present in the JVM. If it's large, that's fine, but including that resource could create a need. It might be better to use a non-existent resource path with a unique name for the system branch. I could assert it doesn't exist and handle a FileNotFoundException. This approach seems to satisfy any concerns about \"remaining uncovered call sites.\"", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_017742b190de04280169f58e02bd7881a0be90a6383f3c1c90\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9Y4U0RveY2A1gBgoaHkMTlPqo-4II5AqlL4VUcBgZ6Jg78TtvKZDOCptKwyoHDIFtBh6YQrUXkg-OyDl8U-xQCqGk81ACjYemMyVpzwCncGSDduN4YHTeh-_PKJzUi7y1UrWN5R1rURtzn0mJkvYibPjo7q47CLbP47e7yk2K4xiPXK25n6nUWmIZvRv9DEH3xSFEI_mR7U_HksDI8OiSE2o3VwZ4l0SbLpUAC3KFv__RmY-z-um7S4JEH659JvlLa3wAuK_-bjTsL_xi_p-jaMfE6PS44ZkAmBlYbsewvhsndEvXczUQ56vy80Bh0stisFnH_MJC1GL0bp3_pVNpQhsXo7MI58ZXYUaTdZIRLZiyWD5YtfsE7Mrc2pxfx9W2KXP51snLdvtyi4qugShKvpaqcYQU4qyi9-u5D5c5-m6ai3aHt_kiY1tLVEvInm9PM13aLHeKiqzOSYQ-u5TfDrSUrGIb5e2OpSUOBeWR-LXyQAa-MnTtMB1A4QmuWYKN0TD7niMOw_WceDu3Yf3lktZV_0HkYA0VbnvwplvzrwtIbKjwBMBkfUF0g4P5AI2QGnM2ZQqAhhJkbFhvLRnDfjzTnRgHwDsVpieNQOrxkTG_WuEhKukBLMhYn2fpa5WZc9v-fkScmp6SZuKiGOLzRPTrK6bXavtsikQJyoeYo50ALEKbI3NhzaUgTUIMJumAPB5bCGzVmJMyHza6Xklm_DeuITmVovDOiesSUjLmSR4D5ojVU5161FpZZ2-Er3kvbr2ob9914fXVoDN-Ifif1RnphceWIvelOE